1 A RESOLUTION recognizing September 17 to 23, 2025, as Constitution Week in
2 the Commonwealth of Kentucky.
3 WHEREAS, the Constitution of the United States, the guardian of our liberties,
4 embodies the principles of limited government in a republic dedicated to rule by law; and
5 WHEREAS, during the summer of 1787, 55 delegates from across the young
6 United States convened at the Pennsylvania State House in Philadelphia with the purpose
7 of establishing a government designed to endure for generations and safeguard the
8 cherished freedoms won through the Revolutionary War; and
9 WHEREAS, the result of their efforts-the Constitution of the United States-stands
10 as the foundation of our nation’s government, embodying the principles of equality under
11 the law and a steadfast dedication to individual liberty; and
12 WHEREAS, our rights and liberties are rooted in the Constitution of the United
13 States and its Bill of Rights, which gave birth to our great nation, and we, as Americans,
14 enjoy our freedom and rule of law through these cherished documents that our founding
15 fathers created; and
16 WHEREAS, September 17, 2025, marks the 238th anniversary of the framing of
17 the Constitution of the United States by the Constitutional Convention; and
18 WHEREAS, celebration of the Constitution of the United States was started when
19 the Daughters of the American Revolution petitioned Congress to set aside September 17
20 to 23 annually to be dedicated for the observance of Constitution Week; and
21 WHEREAS, it is fitting and proper to accord official recognition to this magnificent
22 document and its memorable anniversary, and to the patriotic celebrations which will
23 commemorate it; and
24 WHEREAS, it is fitting that we, the citizens of Kentucky, join the Daughters of the
25 American Revolution in observing Constitution Week from September 17 to 23, 2025, to
26 reflect upon and reaffirm our commitment to the ideals enshrined in this foundational
27 document; and
