1 WHEREAS, the members of the Senate extend their deepest appreciation to the
2 members of the John Guill-Polly Hawkins Craig Chapter of the National Society
3 Daughters of the American Revolution for their unwavering dedication to celebrating our
4 nation's history and hosting Constitution Week celebrations;
5 NOW, THEREFORE,
6 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
7 Kentucky:
8 Section 1. The members of the Senate hereby recognize September 17 to 23,
9 2025, as Constitution Week to celebrate the Constitution of the United States as the
10 cornerstone of our nation’s freedoms, embodying the principles set forth by the framers
11 in 1787.
12 Section 2. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
13 Resolution to Senator Gex Williams.
